Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.19,0:00:02.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love and hate are brought together...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.82,0:00:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Through both reasoning and suspense!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.73,0:00:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today is our 300th episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.24,0:00:08.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One with a sharp resolution full of thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.32,0:00:09.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.95,0:00:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.62,0:00:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.50,0:01:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While we were taking a trip to the Kanmon Straits, the connection point between Honshu and Kyushu...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.92,0:01:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We met a group of four friends, who've known each other since they were high school classmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.26,0:01:57.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the next day...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.26,0:02:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body of Hario Seiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, another one of their classmates, was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.73,0:02:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first, the police suspected the culprit was among these four.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.57,0:02:12.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But all four had seemingly valid alibis, so they were finally excluded from the suspect list.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.99,0:02:14.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.54,0:02:27.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! So that's what happened, huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.63,0:02:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's true, then that person's alibi completely falls apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.34,0:02:40.06,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The Kanmon Straits of Friendship and Murderous Intent
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.80,0:02:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Kanmon Straits of Friendship and Murderous Intent:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.30,0:02:38.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.23,0:02:46.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something about this bothers me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.23,0:02:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what is that something?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.23,0:02:49.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.44,0:02:52.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the "surveillance camera" you noticed earlier mounted in the ceiling?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.94,0:02:55.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one you made a "peace" sign in front of, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:02:56.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.16,0:02:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.53,0:03:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ceiling?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.66,0:03:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Peace!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.17,0:03:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ail\NWhat did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.67,0:03:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there's no way to clearly see his face?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.76,0:03:18.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, because the cameras are only filming from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.47,0:03:21.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so, make no mistake...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:26.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those were the exact the same clothes as the ones in the picture you showed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.06,0:03:29.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.65,0:03:31.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you didn't see his face...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.78,0:03:34.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't be sure it was really Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.78,0:03:37.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan! When did you get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.53,0:03:39.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.20,0:03:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we assume that the man in the tunnel wasn't Hario, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.83,0:03:43.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.91,0:03:47.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, it's probable that Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed a lot earlier than we thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.92,0:03:49.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.08,0:03:54.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The possibility that one of those four people killed Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, still remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.55,0:04:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to have called you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No problem, but why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.81,0:04:10.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad is cruel! It looks he's suspecting you four again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.15,0:04:14.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.36,0:04:19.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, don't you think Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is just as cruel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.07,0:04:22.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Between him destroying your relationship with Hondou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.33,0:04:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An now saying e doesn't even know him...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.49,0:04:28.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's why Hondou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} can't rest in peace, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.79,0:04:33.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.96,0:04:35.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.71,0:04:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really am weird, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.47,0:04:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calling you all the way out here, only to talk about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.80,0:04:44.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You also have someone you love, don't you, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.81,0:04:46.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.06,0:04:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.02,0:04:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.73,0:04:51.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what those people over there are doing...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.60,0:04:55.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That lighthouse is called "The Lover's Lighthouse".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.07,0:04:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Lover's Lighthouse?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.44,0:05:01.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's said that if a couple waves at each other from those two platforms that are close to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.36,0:05:05.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'll be stay together forever, no matter what hardships may occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.80,0:05:17.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.59,0:05:26.26,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: Mt. Hinoyama literally means "Fire Mountain", and is named such because war beacons used to be lit from the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.84,0:05:23.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you rode the ropeway yet? The one on Mt. Hinoyama, that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.47,0:05:26.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.43,0:05:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about we go try it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.64,0:05:29.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.27,0:05:32.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.48,0:05:37.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember right, Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got a call right after we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.61,0:05:41.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that that call came just before 11:00 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.49,0:05:44.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since that was right around the time we met, you see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.12,0:05:49.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you said, Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s testimony is flawless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.58,0:05:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the Kaikyoukan Aquarium?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.96,0:05:56.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's toward the piers, about a five minute walk from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.21,0:06:01.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-So, the Karato Marketplace where Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.13,0:06:03.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The piers where Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got on the ferry...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.80,0:06:06.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally, the Kaikyoukan Aquarium where Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.22,0:06:08.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were all in the same general vicinity?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.81,0:06:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I remember these two people well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.07,0:06:21.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were both very pretty...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.69,0:06:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They received a call from someone in this passage...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.74,0:06:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterward, they went to see the Sea Lion show that started at 11:00 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.37,0:06:33.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.63,0:06:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, say, young lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.00,0:06:44.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man you just talked with told me to ask you something he forgot to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.34,0:06:47.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why of course, young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.35,0:06:55.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems the employees from this food company don't remember having seen Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.98,0:06:57.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.36,0:06:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.69,0:07:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We know for a fact that Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} rode the ferry which left at 11:00 AM...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.03,0:07:06.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Isaka Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and her friend saw him from over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.03,0:07:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} are engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.33,0:07:17.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Nojima Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} also testified that she saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.50,0:07:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the part I can't understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.79,0:07:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.50,0:07:21.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.96,0:07:24.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were following me again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.47,0:07:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} only wears glasses while driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.60,0:07:30.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,G-Glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.97,0:07:36.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When she left the police station yesterday, she had glasses on while she was driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.06,0:07:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.69,0:07:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked the lady from the aquarium and she told me she wasn't wearing glasses at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.28,0:07:46.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, wouldn't it be difficult for her to distinguish something far away?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.57,0:07:49.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.07,0:07:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was used!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.99,0:07:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was used?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.12,0:07:54.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.76,0:08:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.22,0:08:08.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.93,0:08:11.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, this is amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.72,0:08:15.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you used to come here on dates with Hondou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.81,0:08:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.31,0:08:21.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hondou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and I didn't like lively places much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.78,0:08:38.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so, Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, and Okane were always gently watching over and helping us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.34,0:08:43.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.55,0:08:47.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You all were really good classmates, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.76,0:08:50.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To suspect someone among such good people...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.51,0:08:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My dad really is cruel!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.60,0:08:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the cruel one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.40,0:09:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.90,0:09:07.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Isaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} all cooperated to murder Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.86,0:09:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, and then the three of them created an alibi...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.82,0:09:15.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By using Nojima Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.08,0:09:16.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.12,0:09:21.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw from here was not Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, but an impostor!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.00,0:09:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a substitute.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.00,0:09:24.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A substitute?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.63,0:09:28.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would only those three act as accomplices?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.67,0:09:34.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it more natural to think that Nojima Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is also an accomplice?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.47,0:09:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She just met Isaka Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in front of the Kaikyoukan Aquarium.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.73,0:09:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was verified by someone uninvolved with the four, so it must be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.48,0:09:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if we suppose she was an accomplice, wouldn't she have come back from the crime scene with Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.03,0:09:55.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since coming together would have made it easier to stick to their planned schedule than coming separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.20,0:09:56.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.41,0:09:59.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you please gather those four one more time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.87,0:10:02.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I will reveal the whole truth behind this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.46,0:10:03.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.34,0:10:08.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is Azae.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.51,0:10:12.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.18,0:10:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.80,0:10:18.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've just been told that Nojima Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} admitted she was the one who killed Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.35,0:10:20.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nojima Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.48,0:10:22.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.27,0:10:30.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was around 10:00 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.40,0:10:36.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to the hotel where Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was staying and called him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.91,0:10:39.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then led him to a spot close to the Kanmonkyo Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.70,0:10:43.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The place we saw 12 years ago, where Hondou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} took his own life...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.96,0:10:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of how Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} stole his dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:52.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I... begged Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.22,0:10:57.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One word would have been sufficient.\NI just wanted him to apologize to Hondou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.39,0:11:02.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} refused.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.19,0:11:06.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it his choice to commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.19,0:11:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why should I apologize to a piece of trash like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.70,0:11:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before I knew it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.55,0:11:35.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} slowly fell to the ground and stopped moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.39,0:11:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was hit, then fell and stopped moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.77,0:11:47.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, then why...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.52,0:11:52.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you decide to confess?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.36,0:11:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the others to be suspected anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.99,0:12:02.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was my fault, so now I will no longer cause them trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.58,0:12:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On second thought, please gather the other three together and bring them here one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.37,0:12:13.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You still think those three committed the crime together, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.09,0:12:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If not, there are too many points that don't fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.59,0:12:21.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why did Nojima Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} turn herself in and say she was the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.55,0:12:23.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To cover for them...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.26,0:12:23.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.85,0:12:27.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her former classmates and friends, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.48,0:12:30.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I don't think covering for them is a sign of friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.44,0:12:33.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.19,0:12:36.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I think about it like that, all the pieces can come together!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.44,0:12:37.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And once that happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.32,0:12:45.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? When they got the call on their cell phone, they were that surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.95,0:12:46.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.87,0:12:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They quickly rushed out of the shop, both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.25,0:12:53.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.21,0:12:58.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, the true culprit can only be that person'.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.43,0:13:09.60,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Nojima Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} turned herself in, admitting that she killed Hario Seiji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.56,0:13:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't believe her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.90,0:13:19.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akitaya Tooru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Ootsubo Keisuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and Isaka Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.74,0:13:22.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three of you are the true culprits!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.37,0:13:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.79,0:13:28.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please stay quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.41,0:13:30.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Refrain from commenting until after hearing his explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.67,0:13:33.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.08,0:13:37.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he suddenly demanded that you had to ' sell your company, you were fed up with Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.92,0:13:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is probably your motive for killing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.63,0:13:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as you're close friends, Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} supported you in your murder plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.35,0:13:53.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A few minutes after 10:00 AM, the three of you called Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.06,0:13:55.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And killed him under the Kanmonkyo Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.48,0:13:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then you created your alibis like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.40,0:14:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} played Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s role...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.91,0:14:06.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} played Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.41,0:14:11.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on her phone asking her to meet up with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.87,0:14:17.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At 10:15 AM, Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} met Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} at the Kaikyoukan Aquarium, where she asked her to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.13,0:14:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.13,0:14:20.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.88,0:14:30.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called "Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}" at 11:00 AM when it seemed he was boarding the ferry, effectively fooling Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.56,0:14:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the person who was on the pier at the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.56,0:14:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was actually Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wearing Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.53,0:14:40.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.82,0:14:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They took advantage of the fact that your vision is poor, Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.49,0:14:52.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} neither boarded nor rode the ferry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.46,0:14:55.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He hid Otsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s clothes somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.71,0:14:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And hurried to the Karata Marketplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.84,0:15:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to further distance yourselves from the problem, at 11:00 AM...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.22,0:15:09.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} with the phone he had stolen off Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.68,0:15:11.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this about ghosts?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.52,0:15:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you're bored, don't toy with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.82,0:15:24.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Making us think that Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed after 11:00 AM...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.90,0:15:27.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Giving you all seemingly valid alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:32.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In summary, Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} disguised himself as the already deceased Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.66,0:15:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to fill in for\NOotsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s role, Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took his place...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.58,0:15:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took advantage of Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s poor vision
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.30,0:15:45.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.14,0:15:48.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.72,0:15:50.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.18,0:15:53.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though she's your friend, you all too advantage of Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.56,0:15:55.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not true, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.56,0:15:56.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're wrong, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.73,0:15:59.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was the one who killed Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.56,0:16:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you see, Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.11,0:16:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.16,0:16:11.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this be the rumored "Sleeping Kogoro"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.33,0:16:13.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the truth is already...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.91,0:16:17.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,90% happened exactly as I told you just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.46,0:16:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, some points need correction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.54,0:16:22.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.09,0:16:26.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the other three weren't accomplices?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.34,0:16:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also thought they were at first, but that's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.64,0:16:31.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not true?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.72,0:16:32.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.43,0:16:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.64,0:16:41.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got a call on their cell phone while shopping at Moji yesterday until 10:00 AM...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.82,0:16:46.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And according to the store lady, they got very surprised and left in a hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.57,0:16:50.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.32,0:16:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a call from Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.12,0:16:57.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.04,0:17:07.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had probably went to see Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to reject his company acquisition offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.68,0:17:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was when he saw Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who got there before him, accompanying Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.23,0:17:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Worried about Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went after them...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.65,0:17:24.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then saw it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.90,0:17:35.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After finding out what happened from Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s call, Ootsubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Akane{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.83,0:17:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All rushed tot e crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.37,0:17:44.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There, the three worked together to think of a way to cover for Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.25,0:17:49.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Creating an alibi for her with the tricks I just explained to you earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.51,0:17:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did that for me
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.81,0:17:59.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because we're friends, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.44,0:18:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the true culprit is?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.74,0:18:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I was telling you from the beginning!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.11,0:18:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you hit him twice?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.74,0:18:15.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Twice?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.08,0:18:22.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From looking at the body, I noticed signs of being struck in the head twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.71,0:18:26.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Impossible, I only did it once!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.21,0:18:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it's true you struck Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in the head...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.84,0:18:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But at that point, Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't dead yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.01,0:18:38.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking you had killed him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.18,0:18:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} resumed breathing after you fled the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.65,0:18:49.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.15,0:18:55.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was really killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.32,0:18:58.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By receiving another blow to the head...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.33,0:19:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he had resumed breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.83,0:19:05.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the only person who could've done that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.17,0:19:08.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the one who was still at the crime scene after Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.84,0:19:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.84,0:19:12.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... it can only be you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.98,0:19:28.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn her...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.52,0:19:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That bitch, Eiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.03,0:19:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll get you for this...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.87,0:19:43.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's as you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.71,0:19:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was the one who killed Hario.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.13,0:19:51.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.71,0:19:56.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How? How did you know he had started breathing again?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.43,0:20:01.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I inspected his body, I noticed there was a lot of dirt and grass stuck in his nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.89,0:20:06.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there were scratches on the palm of his hand, almost as if he had struggled to get off the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.02,0:20:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s testimony...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.36,0:20:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} slowly fell to the ground and stopped moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.03,0:20:19.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if that was really the case, those scratch marks wouldn't be on his palm.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.24,0:20:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when I understood that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.12,0:20:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had started breathing again after Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fled the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.42,0:20:31.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He held the part of his head that had been struck with his left hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.34,0:20:33.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And put all his strength in his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.59,0:20:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That had to have been a heck of a challenge to lift his body off the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.93,0:20:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's most likely when you gave him the final blow, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.23,0:20:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My company...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.06,0:20:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be damned if Hario forced me to sell my company...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.32,0:20:54.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.40,0:20:55.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.32,0:20:56.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.44,0:20:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it really only because of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.32,0:21:05.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you had left things alone, Hario{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would have probably have reported Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.16,0:21:08.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted to protect Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.83,0:21:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Akitaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
